  "text": "End-to-end integrity checking: The original Onion Routing design did no integrity checking on data. Any node on the circuit could change the contents of data cells as they passed by-for example, to alter a connection request so it would connect to a different webserver, or to 'tag' encrypted traffic and look for corresponding corrupted traffic at the network edges [CITATION_1] . Tor hampers these attacks by verifying data integrity before it leaves the network.",
